  <summary>1/8/2015--Passed House without amendment.
(This measure has not been amended since it was introduced. The summary of that version is repeated here.)

Save American Workers Act of 2015 

This bill amends the Internal&#160;Revenue Code to change the definition of "full-time employee" for purposes of the employer mandate to provide minimum essential health care coverage under the&#160;Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act from an employee who is employed on average at least 30 hours of service&#160;a week to an employee who is employed on average at least 40 hours of service a week.</summary>
</bill>
